  "notes": "Māori (te reo Māori), Eastern Polynesian, New Zealand. Highly regular phonemic orthography: 5 vowel qualities with a phonemic length contrast written with a macron (tohutō: ā ē ī ō ū), 10 consonants, plus the digraphs ⟨ng⟩ /ŋ/ and ⟨wh⟩ (most commonly [ɸ], [f] for many speakers; [ʔw]/[w] in some dialects). Every syllable is open (CV or V). ⟨r⟩ is an alveolar tap [ɾ]. ⟨t⟩ is affricated before /i/ and /u/ for some speakers. Macron spelling is the standard used by Te Taura Whiri i te Reo Māori (Māori Language Commission); older texts double the vowel or leave length unmarked.",
